main event: A farmer discovered a light-weight rock colored black with white spots and greenish portions in Englewood, Ohio on May 30, 1955. The rock had many small holes and had been heated to extremely high temperatures.
interesting points: The rock was extremely hard and had glassy formations, leading the farmer to visit ATIC with evidence.
The U.S. Air Force requested detailed personal information from witnesses for research purposes.

The document contained a questionnaire with various questions related to describing the observed unidentified object or phenomenon, including its motion, brightness, changes in speed, and disappearance from view.
The report also asked if the object was observed through different mediums such as eyeglasses, sunglasses, windshield, and telescopes.
One witness reported observing two white objects, the size of a basketball at arm's length, hovering at an estimated altitude of 3,000 feet. The objects would disappear and reappear.
witnesses: Mr. [redacted], S.D.O., and other individuals who reported UFO sightings
